\subtree{
\title{Quick Start Guide}
\subtree{
\title{For a 15-Minute Conference Talk (PDF Workflow - Recommended)}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Research & Plan} (45 minutes):}
\li{\strong{Use research-lookup} to find 8-12 relevant papers for citations}
\li{Build reference list (background, comparison studies)}
\li{Outline content (intro → methods → 2-3 key results → conclusion)}
\li{\strong{Create detailed plan for each slide} (title, key points, visual elements)}
\li{Target 15-18 slides}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Generate Slides with Nano Banana Pro} (1-2 hours):}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Review & Iterate} (30 minutes):}
\li{Open the PDF and review each slide}
\li{Regenerate any slides that need improvement}
\li{Re-combine to PDF}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Practice} (2-3 hours):}
\li{Practice 3-5 times with timer}
\li{Aim for 13-14 minutes (leave buffer)}
\li{Record yourself, watch playback}
\li{\strong{Prepare for questions} (use research-lookup to anticipate)}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Finalize} (30 minutes):}
\li{Generate backup/appendix slides if needed}
\li{Save multiple copies}
\li{Test on presentation computer}
}

\p{Total time: ~5-6 hours for quality AI-generated presentation}
}

\subtree{
\title{Alternative: PowerPoint Workflow}
\p{If you need editable slides (e.g., for company templates):}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Plan slides} as above}
\li{\strong{Generate visuals} with \code{\startverb --visual-only\stopverb} flag:}
\li{\strong{Build PPTX} using the PPTX skill with generated images}
\li{\strong{Add text} separately using PPTX workflow}
}

\p{See \code{\startverb document-skills/pptx/SKILL.md\stopverb} for complete PowerPoint workflow.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Summary: Key Principles}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Visual-First Design}: Every slide needs strong visual element (figure, image, diagram) - avoid text-only slides}
\li{\strong{Research-Backed}: Use research-lookup to find 8-15 papers, cite 3-5 in intro, 3-5 in discussion}
\li{\strong{Modern Aesthetics}: Choose contemporary color palette matching topic, not default themes}
\li{\strong{Minimal Text}: 3-4 bullets, 4-6 words each (24-28pt font), let visuals tell story}
\li{\strong{Structure}: Follow story arc, spend 40-50\% on results}
\li{\strong{High Contrast}: 7:1 preferred for professional appearance}
\li{\strong{Varied Layouts}: Mix full-figure, two-column, visual overlays (not all bullets)}
\li{\strong{Timing}: Practice 3-5 times, ~1 slide per minute, never skip conclusions}
\li{\strong{Validation}: Visual review workflow to catch overflow and overlap}
\li{\strong{White Space}: 40-50\% of slide empty for visual breathing room}
}

\p{\strong{Remember}:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Boring = Forgotten}: Dry, text-heavy slides fail to communicate your science}
\li{\strong{Visual + Research = Impact}: Combine compelling visuals with research-backed context}
\li{\strong{You are the presentation, slides are visual support}: They should enhance, not replace your talk}
}
}
}